            . On the 18th of December, I was at <placeName id="t17700117-18-crimeloc126">Guildhall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17700117-18-crimeloc126" type="placeName" value="Guildhall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17700117-18-crimeloc126" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700117-18-off124 t17700117-18-crimeloc126"></join>. Just as they had done drawing the tickets, at twelve o'clock, the prisoner was talking to me about a minute or two before, concerning what tickets had been drawn. Presently, Mr. Pain came and tapped me on the shoulder, and said, you have had your pocket picked. I felt, and said, I had lost my neckcloath out of my pocket. Pain ran and laid hold of the prisoner, and said, he was the man that had got it. The prisoner denied it; and Mr. Pain took and pulled it out of his breeches.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17700117-18-person254">
                  William
                   Pain
               <interp inst="t17700117-18-person254" type="surname" value="Pain"></interp>
